All Implemented Interfaces:
CloudsimObservable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Runnable
public class Internet
extends cloudsim.CloudSim
implements CloudsimObservable

The class Internet emulates the function of the real world Internet. The UserBases send their requests to the Internet and the Internet routes those requests to the correct destination DataCenterBroker while inserting the data transfer delay to the simulated requests. The class Internet serves a secondary purpose as the progress updater of the simulation to the GUI. This is not perfect design, but done so to minimize the number of CloudSim entities in the simulation run.

Author:
Bhathiya Wickremasinghe
